title: Ukrainian government criticizes Vega C investigation
summary: The Ukrainian government claims that European investigators were “premature” in concluding that a component from a Ukrainian company was the blame for the failed Vega C launch last December.

title: Investors in space startups see hurdles in defense market
summary: In some sectors of the space industry, innovative technologies from startups don’t stand much of a chance to be part of a DoD program due to institutional and cultural barriers, said Jordan Noone, co-founder and general partner of Embedded Ventures.

title: The small launch industry is brutal—yes, even more than you thought

title: NASA's Curiosity Views First 'Sun Rays' on Mars
summary: The veteran rover captured a dazzling sunset at the start of a new cloud-imaging campaign.

title: Japan’s maiden launch of H3 rocket fails during second stage flight
summary: JAXA and Mitsubishi Heavy Industries launched – at the second attempt – to maiden launch of the H3 launch vehicle at 01:37 UTC Tuesday. However, the vehicle failed shortly after staging, via an apparent failure to light the second stage that was set to deploy the ALOS-3 optical satellite into a 669-kilometer Sun-synchronous orbit (SSO).
